text: Fillière is a commune in the department of Haute-Savoie, southeastern France. The municipality was established on 1 January 2017 by merger of the former communes of Thorens-Glières (the seat), Aviernoz, Évires, Les Ollières and Saint-Martin-Bellevue.Arrêté préfectoral 27 May 2016 == See also == *Communes of the Haute-Savoie department == References == Category:Communes of Haute- Savoie Category:Populated places established in 2017
title: Fillière
